<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911002-0104</DOCNO><DOCID>911002-0104.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Vicon Industries Picks   Darby to Be President</HL><DATE>10/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   VII WNEWS</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MELVILLE, N.Y. -- Vicon Industries Inc. said Kenneth M.Darby was named president, succeeding Donald N. Horn, whoremains chairman and chief executive officer.   Mr. Darby, 45 years old, had been executive vice presidentof the designer and maker of closed-circuit video systems. Hecontinues as chief operating officer. Mr. Horn is 62.</LP><TEXT>   Vicon also said Richard Palke, 44, was named vicepresident for U.S. sales, filling a position that has beenvacant since January. Mr. Palke had been a vice president forsales and marketing at General Instrument Corp., a maker ofcable television, satellite and radar systems equipment.</TEXT></DOC>